com.kuka.geometry

Class SpatialObject

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.kuka.geometry.SpatialObject
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    ICapabilityContainer
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    PhysicalObject, SerialKinematics, VirtualObject, World

    public abstract class SpatialObject
extends Object
implements ICapabilityContainer
    Represents a geometric object that may be part of a scene graph.

    A spatial object can have a parent object and child objects. Thus it can be placed in a tree structure which in most cases is the scene graph.
    Every spatial object has a root frame (see getRootFrame()). Additionally objects can own any number of ObjectFrames that form a tree structure below the object's root frame thus describing the geometric structure of the object.
    Spatial objects can optionally possess information about the object's geometric form (Shape).

    By default spatial objects are transient. They can be made non-transient using setTransient(boolean).

    This class is thread-safe.

    Changes of structure and properties can be monitored by registering for events on getEventProvider(). For further information about available events see TreeEvent and its subclasses.

      • getRootFrame

        public ObjectFrame getRootFrame()
        Gets the root frame of this object.

        A spatial object always has a root frame (ObjectFrame) which cannot be removed.
        This frame never has a parent frame, because it is the root of the frame tree that describes the geometric structure of the object. All frames owned by this object (ObjectFrame.getOwner()) must be part of this tree.

        Returns:
        the root frame of this object.

      • isTransient

        public boolean isTransient()
        Indicates if this object is transient or not.

        Transient objects have a weak connection to the scene graph. This means that they can be removed by a clean up function. Compared to that, non-transient objects have a stronger connection to the scene graph which means that they will not be removed by a clean up.

        Returns:
        true if this object is transient, false otherwise.

      • removeFrame

        public void removeFrame(ObjectFrame frame)
        Removes the specified object frame from the object and disconnects it from its parent frame.

        The frame tree below the disconnected frame stays intact. This operation is not allowed if another spatial object has a connection to the frame to remove (or to any of its descendants), since this would sever the connection to the child object.

        Parameters:
        frame - the frame to be removed.
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - in any of the following cases:
        • the given frame is null
        • the given frame is the root frame of the object
        • the given frame does not belong to this object
        • the given frame is a default frame (see getDefaultAttachmentFrameToParent() and getDefaultAttachmentFrameForChildren()
        IllegalStateException - if another spatial object has a connection to the frame to remove (or to any of its descendants)

      • findFrames

        public Collection<ObjectFrame> findFrames(Predicate<ObjectFrame> predicate)
        Finds all ObjectFrames of this object that match the given Predicate.

        Examples:
        Find all frames with name FrameX:
        Collection<ObjectFrame> xFrames = startFrame.findFrames(frame -> "FrameX".equals(frame.getName())

        Find all frames with name FrameX and distance to Frame otherFrame less than 5.0:
        Collection<ObjectFrame> xFramesWithLowDistance = startFrame.findFrames(frame -> "FrameX".equals(frame.getName()) && frame.calculateDistanceTo(anotherFrame) < 5.0)

        Parameters:
        predicate - the Predicate to be tested against each element that defines whether the element is included in the result.
        Returns:
        all ObjectFrames of this object that match the given Predicate
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - if predicate is null

      • setName

        public void setName(String name)
        Sets the name of the SpatialObject.

        An object name must be unique on the same hierarchy level (i.e. spatial objects under the same parent object must have unique names). Moreover objects representing a resource (i.e. a robot) cannot be renamed.

        Parameters:
        name - the new name to be set. May not be null or empty.
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - if the given name is null or empty
        IllegalStateException - if another object under the same parent already has the given name OR if this instance represents a resource. The name of this object remains unchanged.

      • setTransient

        public void setTransient(boolean isTransient)
        Set the 'transient' property of this object by making it either transient or non-transient.

        Transient objects have a weak connection to the scene graph. This means that they can be removed by a clean up function. Compared to that, non-transient objects have a stronger connection to the scene graph which means that they will not be removed by a clean up.
        Use isTransient() to request the current state of the property.

        Parameters:
        isTransient - the new value of this property
        Throws:
        IllegalStateException -
      • when trying to make this object transient while at least one direct child is not
      • when trying to make this object non-transient while its parent is transient

      • getFrameLock

        protected ReadWriteLock getFrameLock()
        Returns a Lock object that can be used to lock all ObjectFrames owned by this SpatialObject. Using this lock, operations such as traversing frame trees, calculating connections between frames, adding child frames etc. can be performed in a thread safe manner.

        Note: this method only returns the Lock itself! This method does not perform any locking whatsoever. The actual locking will have to be performed by the caller on the returned lock object.

        Returns:
        the Lock object used to lock the entire tree this SpatialObject is part of

      • attachTo

        public void attachTo(SpatialObject target)
        Attaches the default parent attachment frame of this object to the default child attachment frame of the given target object.

        The position and orientation in space of this object is changed by matching the default parent attachment frame to the default child attachment frame of the parent object.

        This operation is only allowed if:

        • The target is another object
        • The target is not part of the object's subtree
        • The target object does not already contain a child with this object's name
        • The target object is non-transient or if both objects are transient
        This method is thread safe.
        Parameters:
        target - the target object where this object should be attached to
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - if any of the arguments is null
        IllegalStateException - if the above conditions are not met
        See Also:
        getDefaultAttachmentFrameToParent(), getDefaultAttachmentFrameForChildren()

        • The target object is non-transient or if both objects are transient

        Throws:

        IllegalStateException - if the above conditions are not met
        See Also:

      • attachWithCurrentPosition

        public void attachWithCurrentPosition(ObjectFrame source,
                                      ObjectFrame target)
        Attaches this object to a parent object with given frames keeping the position in space of this object. This operation is only allowed if:
        • The source frame belongs to this object
        • The target frame belongs to another object
        • The target is not part of the object's subtree
        • The target object does not already contain a child with this object's name
        • The target object is non-transient or if both objects are transient
        This method is thread safe.
        Parameters:
        source - the object frame to be attached to the parent object
        target - the target frame of the parent object where this object should be attached to
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - if the argument is null, or if there is no connection between the given target frame and the given source frame
        IllegalStateException - if the above conditions are not met, or if the relation between the involved frames could not be determined, or there is an unknown connection type between the given target frame and the given source frame
        ThreadInterruptedException - if the thread was interrupted during execution. The thread interrupt flag will be set if the thread was interrupted (that is, Thread.isInterrupted() will return true)

      • isDependentOn

        public boolean isDependentOn(SpatialObject object)
        Tests whether this object is geometrically dependent on the given object.

        In other words the method checks whether this object would be affected by a change to the position or orientation of the given object.

        Example:
        An item within a box is dependent on that box.
        boolean itemDependent = item.isDependentOn(box)

        Parameters:
        object - object to test geometric dependency against
        Returns:
        true if this object is geometrically dependent on the given object, false otherwise.
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - if the given object is null

      • getCapability

        public final <T> T getCapability(Class<T> clazz)
        Gets a specific capability.

        Note: Only exact matching of capability types is supported. Inheritance hierarchy is not considered.

        Specified by:
        getCapability in interface ICapabilityContainer
        Type Parameters:
        T - The type of the requested capability for static type safety.
        Parameters:
        clazz - The Class of the capability to get.
        Returns:
        The capability, never null. Once a capability has been returned, subsequent calls to ICapabilityContainer.getCapability(Class) always return the same capability object for the same Class.
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - if clazz is null
        CapabilityNotAvailableException - if no capability has been associated with clazz.

      • hasCapability

        public final boolean hasCapability(Class<?> clazz)
        Checks whether a capability of the specified Class is available. This is useful to avoid the CapabilityNotAvailableException of the ICapabilityContainer.getCapability(Class) method.
        Specified by:
        hasCapability in interface ICapabilityContainer
        Parameters:
        clazz - The Class of the capability to check.
        Returns:
        true if the requested capability is available, false otherwise. Once true has been returned, subsequent calls for the same Class always return true.
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - if clazz is null

        protected void fireValidationEvent(TreeEvent event)
